{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-jsx","path":"/Neovim/10-adding-color/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"5f7f42e3-3d96-59f7-844e-00fca273dece","html":"<h2>Install colorizer</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      Plug 'norcalli/nvim-colorizer.lua'\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Configuration</h2>\n<p>Create a place for lua plugins</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      mkdir ~/.config/nvim/lua\n\ntouch ~/.config/nvim/lua/plug-colorizer.lua\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>Add the following:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      require'colorizer'.setup(\n  {'*';},\n  {\n    RGB      = true;         -- #RGB hex codes\n\t  RRGGBB   = true;         -- #RRGGBB hex codes\n\t  names    = true;         -- \"Name\" codes like Blue\n\t  RRGGBBAA = true;         -- #RRGGBBAA hex codes\n\t  rgb_fn   = true;         -- CSS rgb() and rgba() functions\n\t  hsl_fn   = true;         -- CSS hsl() and hsla() functions\n\t  css      = true;         -- Enable all CSS features: rgb_fn, hsl_fn, names, RGB, RRGGBB\n\t  css_fn   = true;         -- Enable all CSS *functions*: rgb_fn, hsl_fn\n  })\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<p>Remember to source in <code class=\"language-text\">init.vim</code>, but a little differently this time</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      lua require'plug-colorizer'\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h3>Note</h3>\n<p>This will not work if the file doesn't have and extension i.e. .txt .py. js .css</p>\n<p>If you want to enable it you can do so like this:</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      :ColorizerAttachToBuffer\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Cool Note</h2>\n<p>You can increment and decrement in vim with <code class=\"language-text\">c-a</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">c-x</code></p>\n<p>just hover over a number in normal mode</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">r</code> also work great</p>\n<h2>Lua Note</h2>\n<p>Install <code class=\"language-text\">luarocks</code> if you want to use with <code class=\"language-text\">coc-lua</code></p>\n<h2>Examples</h2>\n<p>Enter the following to see what happens</p>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      #8F6fEa\nrgb(113, 146, 230)\nrgb(7%, 77%, 46%)\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Checkout the repo</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/norcalli/nvim-colorizer.lua\">colorizer</a></p>\n<h2>Install Rainbow</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      Plug 'junegunn/rainbow_parentheses.vim'\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  \n<h2>Configuration</h2>\n<code-fence lang=\"null\" null>\n    <textarea vue-slot=\"code\">\n      let g:rainbow#max_level = 16\nlet g:rainbow#pairs = [['(', ')'], ['[', ']'], ['{', '}']]\n\nautocmd FileType * RainbowParentheses\n    </textarea>\n    </code-fence>\n  ","excerpt":"Install colorizer Configuration Create a place for lua plugins Add the following: Remember to source in , but a little differently this timeâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Adding color with colorizer & rainbow","tags":["neovim"],"image":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/a8734/neovim.png"},"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":3.456140350877193,"src":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/5134e/neovim.png","srcSet":"/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/06f82/neovim.png 197w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/da7d7/neovim.png 393w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/5134e/neovim.png 786w,\n/static/ff1c356d6a7f46604822f50919abcf83/31987/neovim.png 1000w","sizes":"(max-width: 786px) 100vw, 786px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/Neovim/10-adding-color/","prev":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Neovim/08-fzf/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Integrate Neovim with FZF & more","tags":["neovim"]}}},"next":{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/Neovim/09-vim-commentary/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Vim-commentary","tags":["neovim"]}}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}